-- India's HDFC plans to raise at least 5 bln rupees via bonds
-- By Archana Narayanan
-- Thu Mar 13, 2014 02:15AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, March 13 (Reuters) - Housing Development Finance Corp <HDFC.NS>, India's biggest mortgage lender, is planning to raise at least 5 billion rupees ($81.74 million) through three-year bonds with a put option at the end of 13th month at 9.70 percent, two sources with direct knowledge of the matter said.

ICICI Bank and Yes Bank are the arrangers to the bond sale, said the sources.